The moisture content on mass basis was determined as per the 17th edition of Association of Official Analytical Chemists (AOAC)51. Briefly, a known amount of sample was weighed and dried in a hot air oven (Daihan Lab Co., Ltd., Gangwon, Korea) at 105 °C for 4–5 h until constant weight to determine the moisture content and calculated according to the Eq. (1) 52.1%Moisture content=Initial weight-Final weight/initial weight×100.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
